<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="73.[2059,2654,301,723]" pageId="73" pageNumber="468">
<taxonomicName box="[2061,2173,494,527]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="73" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corbeti">S. corbeti</taxonomicName>
was only recently described based on specimens previously attributed to S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1913" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="73" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ollula">ollula</taxonomicName>
, which it might be closely related to. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
