<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="468" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="73.[1444,2651,738,1551]" pageId="73" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1446,1799,1365,1394]" pageId="73" pageNumber="468">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Corbet’s Forest Shrew is only known from the holotype and was only recently described. Corbet’s Forest Shrew seems to have a restricted distribution in a remote region, but additional research is needed to fully resolve its conservation status and needs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
